<br>
Mages are better soloers than Warriors;  that is a fact that won't change.  Mage Epic pets do more damage than Warriors as well.  But Warriors are the tanks.  If you plan on doing something difficult, you have to have a Warrior tank.  Once that role is filled, perhaps you don't need more Warriors.  But the difference is, you can put either a Warrior or a Mage in an auxiliary &quot;damage-dealing&quot; role;  you can NOT put a Mage in the role of tank.  You might as well gripe that some groups want only one Warrior but three Rogues, or nobody wants more than one Cleric or Enchanter in a group.  You might not need more than one of each, but the roles they play are more vital.  Of course, if you plan on only doing boring, easy, non-challenging stuff for your entire EQ career, then fine.  Then again, if that is the case, it almost doesn't matter what your group composition is.<br>
